      <memberdef kind="variable" id="struct_x_dfe_prach___trigger_1adbe3a33690892b419fa84b0eb25c376b" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>u32</type>
        <definition>u32 XDfePrach_Trigger::Mode</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>Mode</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>[0-3], Specify Trigger Mode. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>In TUSER_Single_Shot mode as soon as the TUSER_Edge_level condition is met the State output will be driven to the value specified in STATE_OUTPUT. The Pulse output will pulse high at the same time. No further change will occur until the trigger register is re-written. In TUSER Continuous mode each time a TUSER_Edge_level condition is met the State output will be driven to the value specified in STATE_OUTPUT This will happen continuously until the trigger register is re-written. The pulse output is disabled in Continuous mode:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>0 = IMMEDIATE: Applies the value of STATE_OUTPUT immediatetly the register is written.</para></listitem><listitem><para>1 = TUSER_SINGLE_SHOT: Applies the value of STATE_OUTPUT once when the TUSER_EDGE_LEVEL condition is satisfied.</para></listitem><listitem><para>2 = TUSER_CONTINUOUS: Applies the value of STATE_OUTPUT continually when TUSER_EDGE_LEVEL condition is satisfied.</para></listitem><listitem><para>3 = RESERVED: Reserved - will default to 0 behaviour. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
